Jannik Sinner and Carlos Alcaraz are set to renew their rivalry in the 2025 Cincinnati Open final, which will take place Monday, 3 p.m. EDT/9 p.m. CEST.

Monday's match will mark their fourth consecutive meeting in a tournament final. Sinner won their most recent encounter at Wimbledon, where the Italian defeated Alcaraz in four sets to lift the trophy. With the win, he improved to 5-8 in their Lexus ATP Head2Head series.

